Function Reference/remove all shortcodes « WordPress Codex
-----------

Clears all [shortcode](/Shortcode_API "Shortcode API") hooks.

Usage
-----

` <?php remove_all_shortcodes(); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 (none) 
:   

Return Values
-------------

 (none) 
:   

Examples
--------

Notes
-----

This function clears all of the shortcode tags by replacing the
shortcodes global with an empty array. This is a very efficient method
for removing all shortcodes.

Change Log
----------

Since: 2.5

Source File
-----------

`remove_all_shortcodes()` is located in `wp-includes/shortcodes.php`.

